The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 BHA approaches Pak outfit

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: The city may witness a Pakistan outfit participating in next years Beighton Cup. The Bengal Hockey Association (BHA) has already entered into a negotiation with a Lahore-based team, and is confident about roping them in for the citys premier hockey tournament. 

Confirming the news, BHA secretary Gurbux Singh said on Thursday that the Lahore outfit has shown interest to play the meet even on grass. 

This team boasts of three or four Pakistan national players, Gurbux said. 




